        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/34941",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This is not odd.  When you ask \"$acl->isAllowed('user', 'profile')\" you are asking if the user has access to the profile regardless of the privileged.  The answer to this is \"no\", since there is at least once privilege the user doesn't have access to: \"edit\".\n\nWhen using privileges, this: $acl->isAllowed('user', 'profile') is like saying this: $acl->isAllowed('user', 'profile', '*'), where * is a wildcard.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-09-28T08:45:48.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-09-28T08:45:48.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/34944",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=hipi",
                        "name": "hipi",
                        "displayName": "Andras Hipsag",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Ralph, thank you for your answer.\n\nBut on my logic if I use $acl->allow('user', 'profile') it should override any denies on ('user','profile'), isn't?\nFollowing your logic I guess  $acl->allow('user', 'profile') should mean $acl->allow('user', 'profile','*'), and it definitely should override the previous denies with any privileges.\n\nWhat is wrong with my assumption?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=hipi",
                        "name": "hipi",
                        "displayName": "Andras Hipsag",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-09-28T10:55:32.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-09-28T10:55:32.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
